service ssh status

# SSH (secure shell) is a cryptographic network protocol for operating 
# network services securely over an unsecured network.
# SSH uses public-key cryptography to authenticate the remote computer and
# allow it to authenticate the user, if necessary.
# https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secure_Shell

# service command can used to start, stop, and restart daemons and other 
# services under linux.
